OL,3,CWales' biggest health board to stay in
OL,4,Cspecial measures despite 'some'
OL,5,Cprogress
OL,7,FAccording to the report, the health
OL,8,Fboard also needs to address an
OL,9,Funderlying financial deficit, but is
OL,10,Fmaking "good progress" on financial
OL,11,Fcontrols and management.
OL,13,FHealth Secretary Jeremy Miles said the
OL,14,Fhealth board will continue to be
OL,15,Fsupported "improve and provide
OL,16,Fexcellent care for North Wales."
